      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">BRITISH MUSEUM (NATURAL HISTORY ¶ ), ¶ cromwell road, ¶ london: s.w. ¶ 1 March 1886 ¶ My dear von Mueller,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.03.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From William Carruthers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A39 Royal Geographical Society of Australasia (Vic. Branch) papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by M: 'Answ 19/4/86, FvM'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">BRITISH MUSEUM (NATURAL HISTORY</seg>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">),</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; font-variant: small-caps; ">cromwell road,</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; font-variant: small-caps; ">london: s.w.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; margin-left: 0.493in; text-indent: -0.493in; "
               xml:lang="en">1 March 1886</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.493in; text-indent: -0.493in; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I should have before replied to your letter<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to W. Carruthers, 21 October 1885<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 85-10-21a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as to Forbes' Plants.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Henry Ogg Forbes.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am very glad to hear that you were able to secure so substantial a help for Forbes, and on that account, but yet more on account of the work you have already done on the Papuan Flora you have a right to claim an important part in the description of Mr Forbes' collections. There will be no difficulty in carrying out your proposals. The cellular plants we can deal with here. One of my colleagues — Mr Murray<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>George Murray.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— is devoting himself to Fungi and Algae, and is able to work up whatever materials Mr Forbes may find in these Groups. I have lately had added to my staff a young man from Cambridge, Mr A. Gepp, who obtained a good position at the University, and who is devoting himself to Mosses &amp; Liverworts. I shall try to work out the Ferns. In regard to the Phanerogams my colleague Mr Ridley<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Henry Nicholas Ridley.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>would like to work out the Orchideae — and indeed he would not object to the monocotyledons as a whole. He has charge of that Group in the Herbarium.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Fawcett<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>William Fawcett; see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Proceedings</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of Linnean Society, London, 18 March 1886; Fawcett (1886).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>took a great interest in Forbes's Ericaceae and would be glad if he could take charge of any further specimens, and has just communicated a paper to the Linnean Soc. on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Balanophoreae</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Rafflesiaceae</hi>
               </seg>, and these he would like to continue.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I fear you think I am going on rapidly to make of no effect what I allowed at the beginning, but my claims stop here.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In regard to the distribution. The whole collections will, I expect come here and be distributed by us into sets. I would take care that the second set should be sufficient for your purposes — and in any cases where uniques existed I would be prepared to send them on to you for description to be returned when you were done with them.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Of course if you would like to work up some of the monocotyledons we can easily arrange that.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In regard to Myoporums I am sorry to say we have no specimens from Forster, father or son<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to W. Carruthers, 3 December 1885, in this edition as 85-12-03a.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— and only<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">M. crassifolium</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is represented in the Herb. and that by specimens collected by Anderson<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>William Anderson.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>at New Caledonia 1774 — the same voyage in which the Forsters were with Cooke<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Error for James Cook.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— I enclose a leaf &amp; two flowers from Andersons plant. I am sorry I cannot do more.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would it be possible to secure a set of the plants of Everill's expedition up the Fly River?<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn9" n="10">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Geographical Society of Australasia's expedition to New Guinea under Henry Charles Everill, 1885.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I would very much like to have a series for the Herbarium.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I trust these proposals will be approved by you, &amp; am</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">very sincerely yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W. Carruthers</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Balanophoreae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ericaceae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Myoporum crassifolium</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Orchideae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Rafflesiaceae</p>
         </div>
